BFN 

  [Text] Another meeting of the bilateral expert group from 
the Russian and U.S. defense departments began in Moscow on 
Wednesday. 
  A spokesman from the Defense Ministry's information and 
press 
department has told Interfax that for three days experts will 
discuss issues associated with European security, the situation 
in Bosnia, and problems on Russia's joining the Partnership for 
Peace program. The two sides also intend to exchange views on 
nuclear safety cooperation and the reduction and further 
elimination of wapons of mass destruction. 

