<H3> <TI>   Missiles Detargetted by 30 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Missiles Detargetted by 30 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0605082394 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0630 GMT 6 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0605082394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow 2x2 Television </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 30 May, Russian strategic missiles with nuclear 
warheads will no longer be aimed at targets located on the 
territory of the United States and Great Britain. This was 
announced by Colonel-General Igor Sergeyev, commander in chief 
of the Strategic Rocket Troops. According to him, the missiles 
will not be aimed at any target in the world. 

</TEXT>

