<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The joint commission on compliance and inspection is 
continuing its work in Geneva. This temporary body was set up 
to implement the treaty on reduction of strategic offensive 
weapons, START-1 and START-2. Representatives of five powers -- 
Russia, Ukraine, Belarus, Kazakhstan, and the United States -- 
belong to the commission. Ukraine, Belarus, and Kazakhstan are 
to join the treaty as non-nuclear states. [begin recording] 
  Russian Representative M. Streltsov -- identified by 
caption: We have already made a certain amount of 
progress. A whole series of agreements and joint statements by 
our commission have been signed. 
  These regulate issues involved in the multilateral 
fulfillment of the treaty. We believe that the Ukraine will 
accede to the nuclear non-proliferation treaty in the very near 
future. This will create all conditions necessary to ensure 
that the treaty comes into force. [end recording] 

