<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 7 TASS -- Finnish representatives have 
held an inspection in the Leningrad military District in 
accordance with the 1992 Vienna document of negotiations on 
confidence-building measures and security. 
  The Finnish Government requested the Russian Government on 
May 2 to hold the inspection in the area of Alakurtti, Polyarnye 
Zori, Primorskiy and Selkyalya in the Leningrad Military 
District the Russian Defence Ministry's Information and Press 
Department reported today that the Finnish request has been 
satisfied. The four-member Finnish inspection group arrived in 
the aforesaid area on May 4 and held a 48-hour inspection. 

</TEXT>

