<H3> <TI>   Nuclear Test Ban Debated </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nuclear Test Ban Debated </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Defense Experts Call For Resumption of Nuclear Tests </H4>

<F P=102> BR1305131494 Paris LE QUOTIDIEN DE PARIS in French 13 May 94 
p 4 </F>

<F P=103> BR1305131494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris LE QUOTIDIEN DE PARIS </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On Tuesday [10 May], Arthur Paecht, the rapporteur 
of the military programming law, declared that, "according to a 
unanimous recommendation of all experts consulted, the 
resumption of nuclear tests is indispensable." As to the Palen 
test simulation program, it "would not suffice to ensure the 
development of new nuclear charges." The deputy also pointed to 
two other "controversial" issues: "The decision by the 
president of the Republic to keep active the ballistic missiles 
on the Albion plateau" and "the five-year delay in the M5 
strategic ballistic missile program." 

</TEXT>

