<F P=103> BK0905111994 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Summary] Australia has ratified the Chemical Weapons 
Convention. The ratification deposited with the United Nations 
in New York means Australia is the sixth country to ratify the 
convention. Since the convention opened in January last year, 
157 countries [word indistinct]. The convention banning 
chemical weapons will take effect after it is ratified by 65 
countries. Australia's foreign minister, Gareth Evans, said 
Australia's ratification ensured it would continue to play a 
leading role in efforts to get a global ban on chemical weapons. 

