<F P=100> LATIN AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> COLOMBIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Operation Targets Precursor Chemicals </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Operation Targets Precursor Chemicals </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94WD0302A Santa Fe de Bogota EL ESPECTADOR in Spanish 11 Mar 
94 p 11A </F>

<F P=103> 94WD0302A </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota EL ESPECTADOR </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota -- In a crackdown on the drug 
traffic, the Antinarcotics Police conducted a series of 
operations resulting in the seizure, in several of the country's 
cities, of a total of 1,754 chemical substances and elements 
used for processing cocaine and other hallucinogens. 
  The operation, called "Volatil Uno," was carried out in the 
Cundinamarca locality of Mosquera, and in the cities of 
Medellin, Barranquilla, Cali, Pereira, Bucaramanga, Ibague, and 
Cartagena. 
  The largest confiscation took place in the Atlantico 
capital, 
where over 1,014 tons of those products were seized. 
  It was reported from Bucaramanga that thousands of gallons 
of 
acids and hundreds of kg of other substances were confiscated 
from a factory apparently being operated illegally. In 
connection with it, however, the amounts of components stored 
were found not to coincide with those registered by the supplier 
firm. 
  Included among the components seized were butyl acetate, 
ethyl acetate, hydrochloric acid, sulfuric acid, ammonia, 
butanol, both dense and light sodium carbonate, hexane, N.E.K. 
[expansion not given], methanol, toluene, and different types of 
solvents. 
  The police attached particular significance to the 
confiscation of these types of precursors, because their control 
is one of the fundamental points in the strategy devised by the 
national government to battle the drug trafficking Mafias. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

