  [Text] New Delhi, Feb. 27 (UNI [United News of India]): 
Pakistan has dumped tonnes of narcotics along the Rajasthan 
border and the drug pedlars are waiting for security lapses to 
push the contraband into India, according to the Border Security 
Force (BSF) chief, Mr. D.K. Arya. 
  The drugs are worth hundreds of crores of rupees in the 
international market. The move is a part of Pakistan's larger 
strategy to weaken India economically and expose New Delhi to 
international pressure in yet another arena -- Narco-terrorism. 

