  [Text] Bombay, March 5: A Ugandan woman, allegedly carrying 
3.5 kg of heroin concealed in the false top and bottom of her 
suitcase, was caught at Sahar airport on Thursday. 
  Margaret Wasswa was on her way to Addis Ababa by an 
Ethiopian 
airlines flight when she was stopped by officials at the airport 
on suspicion. It was found that she had smeared the heroin with 
chili powder to mask the odour of the drug, officials said. 
  Wasswa was asked details of the hotel in which she had 
stayed 
in Bombay but, officials say, she could not give any. "She 
however stated that the heroin was to be delivered to her 
associate abroad and that she got the suitcase containing the 
drug in the Colaba area near a five-star hotel," officials said. 
She has been remanded to custody upto March 17. 

