<TEXT>
CSO 

  [Text] Bombay, March 5: Four kg of heroin, foreign and 
Indian currency totalling Rs 5 crores were seized by customs 
officials from four persons, two foreigners and two Indians, 
here on Thursday. 
  On following a tip-off, officials went to the Breach Candy 
swimming pool and arrested Jackson, a Finn, as he was passing on 
a packet to a British national, Martin. The packet contained 30 
grammes of heroin, officials said. Interrogation of the duo led 
the police to a flat in Venus Apartment, Altamount Road, 
revealed that Jackson had allegedly stashed away large amounts 
of currency and a trans-receiver. 
  Even as officials searched the apartment, an Indian, Manoj 
Singh, walked in. He too was interrogated and he revealed that 
he had come accompanied by his mother, Rajmani Singh alias 
Mishra, to deliver heroin to Jackson. The Singhs further led the 
officials to another flat in Savitha Apartments at Versova, from 
where some more heroin and currency was seized by the officials. 
Further investigations are on. 

