<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Yuriy Shcherban] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 28 Apr -- A two-day conference at the 
Russian Ministry of Internal Affairs [MVD] of directorates and 
departments engaged in the struggle against drug dealing and 
drug addiction representing the internal affairs bodies of 14 
states -- the former republics of the USSR (only a 
representative of Tajikistan was missing) -- ended today. 
  Aleksandr Sergeyev, head of the directorate of the Ministry 
of Internal Affairs of the Russian Federation for combatting 
illegal drug dealing, told journalists that the conference had 
discussed basic areas of cooperation. 
  In reply to a question from an ITAR-TASS correspondent, 
Sergeyev said that in 1993 in Russia there were about 53,000 
crimes connected with drug addiction or illegal drug dealing -- 
83 percent more than in the 1980's. In 1993, 53 tonnes of 
narcotic substances had been confiscated, and 500,000 people had 
been charged. 

</TEXT>

