<F P=106> [Report by Ciro Ortega for the "RPC Television News" </F>
newscast] 
  [Excerpts] Ernesto Perez Balladares, presidential candidate 
of the United People alliance, went to the San Fernando Hospital 
for a drug test, which came out negative. Perez Balladares 
stressed that if he wins the presidential elections, he will 
implement a vigorous policy against drug trafficking. 
  [Begin recording] [Perez Balladares] I came for a drug test 
because I think the Panamanian people have the right to demand 
and to know whether their candidates are using chemical 
substances. I also had a stress test because I think the next 
president should have enough physical stamina and be in good 
enough health to keep the promises made to the Panamanian people. 
  [Ortega] Could this be viewed as a prelude to your 
government's policy against drugs? 
  [Perez Balladares] You can be sure that if I took the test, 
I 
will demand that everyone else do likewise. [passage omitted] 
  [Ortega] Why did you take the drug test? Have other 
candidates done the same? 
  [Perez Balladares] I hope we all do it. I think it should be 
done as a sign of respect for the Panamanian people so they can 
be sure that none of us use any type of chemical substance. [end 
recording] [passage omitted] 

