<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Narcotics Roundup 2-8 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Narcotics Roundup 2-8 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0905070394 </F>
<F P=103> BK0905070394 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on narcotics developments in South Asia, Southeast Asia, 
and the Pacific monitored by Bangkok Bureau between 2 and 8 May 
1994. Source information is given in parentheses after each item. 
<H8>  SOUTH ASIA </H8>
<H5>  Nepal </H5>
<H5>  Authorities Arrest 13, Seize 100 Kg of Hashish </H5>
  An Army patrol arrested 11 people carrying 100 kg of hashish 
inside of the Royal Bardiya Wildlife Conservation Area on 7 May 
and handed them over to police. Police later arrested the 
group's leader Bhupal Khatri and another person in a hotel. The 
leader reportedly admitted to smuggling 305 kg of hashish into 
India on three previous occasions. (Hong Kong AFP in English 
0752 GMT 8 May 94) 
<H5>  Pakistan </H5>
<H5>  Customs Intercepts 410 Kg of Hashish, Arrests One </H5>
  Officers at the Khorkhera Customs post intercepted a truck 
travelling from Quetta to Karachi on 22 April. They found 410 
kg of hashish hidden in secret compartments. The driver 
escaped, but two passengers were arrested. (Karachi DAWN in 
English 24 Apr 94 p 3) 
<H8>  SOUTHEAST ASIA </H8>
<H5>  Philippines </H5>
<H5>  Narcotics Command Arrests Four `Big-Time Drug Dealers' in </H5>
Laguna 
  Narcotics Command agents arrested Ricardo Alikbuson, Ermita 
Salandanan, Gener Vallejo, and Eduardo Nagora--all "big-time 
drug dealers"--during a raid in Santa Rosa, Laguna in which more 
than 1 kg of methamphetamine hydrochloride was confiscated. 
(Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network in Tagalog 
0930 GMT 6 May 94) 
<H5>  Thailand </H5>
<H5>  Macao Man Arrested With 1.5 Kg of Heroin, AK-47 </H5>
  On 2 May, Police in Bangkok arrested Macao citizen Lai Seng 
Po, 29, and charged him with possessing an AK-47 assault rifle 
and 1.5 kg of heroin. The suspect had allegedly hijacked a taxi 
and wounded the driver. (Bangkok BANGKOK POST in English 3 May 
94 p 3) 
<H5>  Kenyan Arrested With 43 Kg of Heroin </H5>
  A Kenyan national who identified himself as J.N. Okafor, 23, 
was arrested on 6 May. His passport identified him as Charles 
Bamaba. On 5 May, police discovered three fertilizer sacks 
containing 115 bars of heroin base weighing a total of about 43 
kg hidden inside four large plastic sacks of jeans at a shipping 
company in Suan Mali, Pom Prap Sattru Phai district. The Kenyan 
suspect was arrested by a Metropolitan Police antinarcotics team 
when he came to collect the package. (Bangkok BANGKOK POST in 
English 7 May 94 p 3) 
<H5>  Vietnam </H5>
<H5>  Border Defense Forces Seize Vessel Loaded With Marijuana </H5>
  Border defense forces under the management of Naval Group 28 
recently intercepted a ship in Vietnamese territorial waters 
near Tho Chu Island in Kien Giang Province. The ship did not 
have any flag, vessel name, or registration number. Authorities 
found 18 people of different nationalities on board along with 
1,758.90 kg of marijuana bound for Indonesia. The marijuana was 
reportedly loaded at Koh Kong, Cambodia. An American identified 
as John was reported to be in command of the smuggling 
operation; he claimed he was on a sightseeing trip in Cambodia 
when he boarded the ship, and the drugs were already there. 
(Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 1100 GMT 8 May 94) 

</TEXT>

